\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What year were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 I was born the fifth of August 1902.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And that was here in Fetlar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, Tresta Fetlar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And you've not married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How many years did you live at the house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh - well I lived until I was eighteen and then I went to Sir Watson's at Lea and then I was ni
ne and a half years there but you see I was always come back and forth home. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So from when you were born until 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, 'til 1920 I was living in Tresta.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 In the same house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Just one sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When was she born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 She was born in August 1905.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 A bit younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How old was your father when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 couldna}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
 really tell you that. Oh he'd been in his forties. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 He came from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 Unst}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  in - November of 1872 to Fetlar. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did he work at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 He was a crofter fisherman. But he worked on the croft in the wintertime and he went to the fishing in the month of May down as far 
as Fraserburgh and sometimes they went up the Minch and up to the Western Isles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did he have any other jobs apart from crofting and fishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No. Well you see he worked about the croft and he was very good at shoemaking and all that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did he earn money by that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, he didna really earn money by that. The crofting and the fishing was the industries.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 He didn't have any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no. That was - filled all his time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 That's what he was 'til he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You don't remember him ever being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, he was never out of work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How old was your mother when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well she'd been in her thirties - seven I'm not sure exactly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did she come from }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 Unst}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, she was born at - across the Urie house across the valley from the Post Office.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Here in Fetlar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, in 1857.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did she have any jobs before she was married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, just working about croft and she used to work fo
r the gutting, gutting herrings over at Uyeasound in the summer. So, a lot of the Shetland women went to the gutting, that was before they got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 these}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  gutting instruments.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Where was the gutting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 In Uyeasound, Unst. Yes, yes Unst.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So she went there at what time of the year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh from June to - August.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 That was fairly regularly was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well it was certain summers they were there. War come on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Why was it given up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well you see the British, they lost their trawlers and all that and they never got them back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So fishing fell away after the first war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, the fishing fell away. Is it recording now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did she have any jobs after you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, just look after the house and the children, my sister and I and they used you see to cure the peats and - clean the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 potatoes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  and all - do all the country work during the summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How many rooms were there in your house here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well there was two. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did anyone else besides your sister and parents live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 I had an aunt that stayed with us, me father's sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 She was living there permanently was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, she was there permanently until she died. My mummy and aunty both lived 'til they were eighty-six an
d they had all their senses. Yes, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, always done at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Mother used to help to make the clothes and daddy used to help to mend our boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were the clothes new or secondhand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, they were - it was what was new - we got was new and then we used to patch it you know and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Where did you get the new clothes, where were they bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we could get them bought in Lerwick. And - knitted jumpers you see for ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What kind of clothed did they make for themselves then, jumpers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. And - well, scarves you know, they wear over their head.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But your mother didn't make her own dresses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Not much, no, no, no, not much. She used to make maybe, well, you know, everyday wearing things but not for better wear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house, like cleaning and cooking and decorating and washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, he was always too busy with the other work to - take time for that. And she wasna ailing for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did he do things like improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes, he always did - did anything like that, painted the windows and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did he bath the children or dress them or undress them or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, that was left to the women.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did he read to you or tell you stories?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes. I remember him learning me to read and learning me to tell hymns. If I come to Jesus and all that kind of thing. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 I suppose your aunt would have looked after you when your mother went out, not your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes. Yes, yes, there were always - she was always there to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you have any tasks you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we always had to help to clean the house and - wash the dishes and do anything we could to help. Then whe
n we got a bit bigger we helped out in the fields you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But did you have any particular tasks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, not just specially.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you help your sister, she was younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you help look after her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you have to put her to bed and dress here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, no, she was only three years a difference you see so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we usually went to bed at about ten o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, mummy put us to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 At what age did you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Maybe eight or nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you share the bedroom with anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, me sister and I.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you share the bed or did you have your own beds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, we were in the same bed, we - the - well me father and mother had one bed in the room and - me sister and I had another one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 In the same room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, in the same room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about your aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well she had a - small bed in the kitchen end.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you have baths in those days at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no. We would - we had a zinc bath you know but no water laid on and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But you did have a zinc bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Where did you use that, in which room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we'd be using the kitchen you see in front of the fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How often did you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh we had clean clothes every week and - and oftener if we needed them. Oh aye, very clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How often did you have baths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well once a - well the children was bathed every night but when we got bigger then once a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Which room did you have your meals in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 That's where your mother cooked as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did she cook on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Well it was an open fire to begin with and it had hooks you know and a kettle and we had what they call a dutch oven for baking bread. Have you ever - have ever seen a dutch oven? It's a round and has a lid and we used to have a fine big peat
 fire and then some of the - take some of the coals and lay on the top of that, made the heat at the top. It made nice bread - scones inside that oven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When did you have some different kind of equipment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh - we got the - well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 American}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  stoves in after the first world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So up to and during the war you had an open fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes. Yes, yes. Always plenty of peats then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What time did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh we had breakfast about nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And were all the family there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Father and mother and you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did you usually have to eat and drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 We always had porridge and we always had plenty of milk for we'd cows and cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you have anything else besides porridge?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, nothing but the tea and bread and porridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You didn't have eggs or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about the midday meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well you see they always had plenty of fish usually. They would catch them in the su
mmer and then they would salt them and we'd have salt fish and they always had plenty of bacon. They had two pigs usually, they killed the bigger one before Christmas and - nice dried hams you know and smoked ham and then they would boil the smaller piece
s of pork you know. And then they would kill the younger pig before the year. That was before the spring work started. So they always had plenty - and they had hens you see and we could have eggs and have hen cooked now and again.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So usually for lunch you'd have pork or fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Or - fish probably. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What sort of vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well that - we always potatoes and we had turnips if we had soup and cabbage in the soup too. We grew plenty of cabbage then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Would you have any sort of pudding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Not very often, no. Only later years when we got the puddings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about the evening meal, when would you have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we had tea about five o'clock you see. Tea and scones and butter, jam, we grew rhubarb, we could make rhubarb ja
m. And then the Shetland folk used to have cup of tea about eight o'clock and then they would have some - well tea and anything else that they wanted maybe between nine and ten for their evening meal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What would you have in the late evening then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well maybe - a bit of fried pork or something like that. But it wasn't a heavy meal you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you have anything different on certain days like Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes, there were always something better on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What was better?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well - well we always had soup on Sunday then. Soup usually - made - well always make a nice pork - made nice cabbage soup you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Anything else special on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well you usually had boiled eggs for breakfast on Sunday. And - they could always have eggs you see any time, for tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You told me your mother made her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And she made rhubarb jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Any other things she made at home like wine or medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did she bottle any fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 There's no fruit to bottle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 She didn't brew any beer at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your father and mother grow their own vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 They grew cabbage and turnips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, and all big patches of potatoes, the po
tatoes did you see for the whole year round and they always had plenty, some to give to the animals as well and - cows got turnips and - cabbage, in the winter along with straw and hay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were there other vegetables in the garden which you ate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, not until later on when they grew bigger, then we learned to grow the carrots and that sort of thing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But that was after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, after the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did they buy any tinned fruit or vegetables or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Not before the war, no, no, there was nothing of that at the shop then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did they keep in the way of livestock on the croft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well the crofts were about six acres of arable and then they had an outrun and a scaddle for thirty-two sheep, or six ponies
 and two sheep. And - well they grew the - corn - corn you know for to feed the animals and they reaped the hay and grew potatoes and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 turnips}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  and cabbage.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What animals did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 We had - well he had three cows you see and usually two young 
ones. And five or six ponies for getting home the peats. And a bigger one for carting out the manure and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And two pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How many sheep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh well, we had nigh a dozen sheep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we had a bout a dozen hens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Anything like geese or ducks or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, we didn't have them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Who looked after the animals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well me father and mother looked after them and when he was away then me mother and aunt looked after them during the summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you look after them as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, when we grew up then we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 helped}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  to look after them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How many times a week did you have meat to eat, fish or pork, would it be every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, there were always something, fish or meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you ever get anything like rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, there plenty of rabbits down here in the links.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food at any time so that the family could have more?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, no there was never like that up here. They'd plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were children supposed to keep quiet then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Not very - they werena so cheeky then as they are nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, we usually ate what was cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What was your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 parent\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  attitude if you left some food uneaten on your plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh - they werena really }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 angry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  but they always liked when we finished up what we got.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 If there was something on the table that you wanted, like the salt, could you ask someone pass it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You wouldn't have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, well to have table manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, we didn't usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well when we were finished.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But did you all get down together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, well I mean the bairns sometimes got off you know before the older folk for they were maybe no finished eating, but
 we didna scurry very far away. Just maybe up to the fireside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Me mummy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What order were you served in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well the older folk always go first. Then the children afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about you and your sister, were you served first because you were older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, usually, 'cos I was a bit older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Where did your sister sit before she could feed herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh she usually sat by me mummy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And your mother would have fed her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you find your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did she show you much affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. Just the usual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 If you had any worries could you share them with her or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, he was quite nice to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Could you talk to him as easily as to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Would you talk to him about problems in the same way as you would to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Maybe not exactly but he was always very kind and friendly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we always behaved with courtesy you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did courtesy mean though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well - please and thank you and mall that sort of thing. We didna grab things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Any other things they expected of you in that kind of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well the bairns was used to say their grace before they started their meal. And a wee bit of prayer when you went to bed at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your parents bring you up to behave towards your sister in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did they say you should hit back or not if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No. You just usually got on very well, never had any fights. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you would grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well they hoped that we would grow up to be sensible and honest and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your parents bring you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes, honest and - honesty and truthfulness and all that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Honesty and truthfulness were the main things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Any other things that emphasised?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well cleanliness too. Yes. Oh, just the essentials of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh - that was usually old men's phrase.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But if you'd sworn?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, I - we never swore anyhow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 They }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 wouldn't}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
 have liked it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well sometimes, when it was anything we could join in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But there wasn't anything like children should be seen and not heard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 If you did something your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well I never got a thrashing. No, no. But they were maybe a bit angry sometimes if we did something they thought wasna right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did they punish you in any way at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You weren't stood in the corner or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, no we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did they just get angry or was there any kind of discipline or punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, not for us lasses. Nos.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When it was a matter of showing }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4195931\charrsid4750000 disapproval}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  - was it more your father or your mother who did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Well you see, mother was usually more with us than me father. So - we - we maybe stood a bit more dread of him if he was home and we were naughty but werena really that bad.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Would you say that you received the ideas you had about how to - behave from both your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Or did one play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, both of them really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When you had a birthday would it be different from any - other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, mummy
 used to bake a - scone with some currants in it maybe. We had something different likely. You see, we - my birthday and me sister's was just a fortnight the difference you see. Mine was the third of August, hers was the seventeenth, so one year we had a 
wee party in a way on my birthday and the next year on hers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When you say a party, did you have friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well turn and they used to - well they were all next door neighbours and they used to come over to us and then we used to go over them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you have any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And you used to have a cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, well - maybe a - a few sweets from the shop. You could get quite a lot of sweeties for a tanner then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Can you remember anything you did with your mother or father together on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Well you see when we were young all the young men they used to play football down here on the links. That was every Christmas. But the girls, well they just usually - had any sort of - well, maybe - liked amusement at home
, they never were down on the links playing football.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But did you do anything special at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, but I know nothing was done at Christmas. No, we didn't do any knitting at Christmas.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you have a special meal or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well they usually had something better maybe on Christmas Day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Presents and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No. Not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Father Christmas or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well if they thought there was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 Santa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  Claus you know and the bairns got something in their sock. Yes. But there was nothing very special. Yes, we always knew - they always knew about Santa. Got an apple and an orange maybe, Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you have any musical instruments in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No. Lots of folk did but we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well my sisters a good singer but - but we were not very musical.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So you didn't make music together in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you sing together at all then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well, she could sing a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 She would sing to you at home sometimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your parents play any games with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we used to play simple card games sometimes you know. Just simple card games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well I - they used to play draughts sometimes, but not just very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What sort of books did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we always got, you see, Sunday school prizes in those days and we could borrow some from the folk around the neighbourhood
. They had children, oh long before us, and they kept their Sunday school prizes and that and we would get a loan of them and read them and give them back again. And there was a lend library at the school when we went there. Jane P Coates gave that. And -
 
and in the summer time you see we went to the Sunday school down here at the church and - and when the Sunday school was finished in November then we came down here to the Manse and every Saturday afternoon and Mrs Campbell, well she taught us bits of poe
try and them that could sing did bits of singing and then well like after the New Year we had a little concert down the kirk. Far more folk then than now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your parents own any books themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well they had a few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 The Bible?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, always had a Bible and the shorter catechism and books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about newspapers and magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well there was the Shetland Times, that came around but they never bother much with - you see there was no paper so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you have any magazines, church magazines or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, we used to get the Life and Work occasionally. But it wasna once a month like now I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you remember your mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes. They both read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did they ever read aloud to you or each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes. No, no, they - mum'd read a little out to us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What kind of things would she read aloud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well - before we could read the story books to ourselves then she would read to us. My auntie read to us often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you remember a funeral in your family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, not until I was quite grown up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So you don't have any memories of a funeral that took place before the first war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no. No family, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were you taken out visiting friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes. Yes, yes, now we could go and visit any of the neighbours any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you go with your parents to visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, now we could go with them when we were small and then when we grew bigger we'd go on our own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 At what age would you go out visiting on your own then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Maybe when we were ten or eleven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were you taken shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You see the shop was just right across the road. So we could get there when we were maybe five or six with a simple message.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you ever go out just with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you remember any outings with your parents, like on Bank Holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you ever go to Lerwick, that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well I never went to
 Lerwick until in the early 1920's, for you see I wasn't old enough to go before the war and then the war come on and - I wasn't away. And I went to Lee Garth, service, in August 1920. And it was when I had a holiday from there, a week or two then, we usu
ally went down to Lerwick for this holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So you didn't leave the island at all until after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, not 'til after war. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 Except - well I - I was once over in mid Yell. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Me mummy used to go over and sell hosiery in mid Yell, we used to knit shawls }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  see, and all that, that was before the jumble work came on, and what we knitted when we were small was the fine hosiery you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So your mother took it over mid Yell to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 sell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But you only went there once yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Yes, I was once over in Yell with her. In the summertime. We went with the post boat. With a rowing boat you know, but the boat could sail. There was no engines then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days, was it the same as any other day or was it different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Well you see, we didn't go to school on Saturday. But we would help at home and maybe go and visit our friends or have some of them around the houses to see us and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we went to kirk on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How many times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Well the bairns went in the morning when we - I remember going down to the kirk here in May in 1910 when they got telegram to say that King Edward was died. There }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 was no telephone}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  then, the minister got a telegram to say that the King was dead.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 read}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
 it out in the kirk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Yes, they opened the kirk. And they'd be all marched to Brough and had a party there for the coronation in 1911. All the schoolchildren, marched with flags and so on and we had quite a nice party over at Sir Arthur }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 Nicholson\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  at Brough Lodge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How many times did you go to the kirk on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we always - Sunday morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You didn't go in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Not much in the evening, no. But the folk went. All the folk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you have different clothes on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What was different then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we always had something better on Sunday and we had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you play any games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, we weren't allowed to play games on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your parents think it was wrong to work on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
They never did anything unless what was necessary. They never worked out in the fields like they do now. On Sundays. They used to bring in the water and all - you see we had to carr
y the water then - used to have it in a big barrel at the door what we needed for over the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 weekend}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 . All that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You did the minimum amount of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, a minimum amount of work on Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And your parents went to church, this was the Church of Scotland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, Church of Scotland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How often did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well they would go usually in the morning and sometimes if they could get in the evening as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 That was both your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And you went to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Was the Sunday school different from the main service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Yes, yes, the Sunday school was - was after the service, and the minister's wife, Mrs Campbell, took the very wee ones. Then an elder took the n
ext size and - oh there were a lot of bairns then. And then when once the folk had joined the Church when they were maybe sixteen or eighteen and Mr Campbell had them in a class upstairs
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 That was after the service?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, it was all after the service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were there any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You didn't have any sort of parties or fetes or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, not really. I remember us once having a party down here in the Manse garden but I really don't know what that w
as to commemorate. It was just a party down here in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were there any social activities organised by the church that you took part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, not of more than that concert and you see that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 There was a concert?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But you had to rehearse for that didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Yes, yes, do something. And then during the winter the women used to do knitting and then Mrs Campbell used to have a small sort of party for the women and they would give always an article of knittin
g and that you see was sent to Edinburgh for to - well to give to the funds of the Church of Scotland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 There were no activities for young people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, not much, they - well they would have dances you see. There was no public hall then and if they
 was a wedding they had it in the school. But they would maybe have it in some of the bigger crofting houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But there weren't any activities to do with the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, we'd no outings or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Was there anything like a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No. Mrs Campbell used to have a - well a - Bible Class and when Mrs Campbell would have the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 Women\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 ' Guild.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you go to the Bible Class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, I - the boys went to the Bible Class and the women went to the knitting.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And you said grace at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And you and your sister said it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Sometimes. Maybe on Sunday evening. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you know if your father took any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
I don't think it was much. There was only an old man, Mr Wesson that used to be a Liberal member for Shetland but I don't think he was ever in this island.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you know what your father's political views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh they were all Liberals, Shetlanders I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Your mother didn't take much interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh no, she - there were no much - activities in politics then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you remember an election after the war in 1919, do you remember your parents voting in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
No, I don't really remember that but I remember the voting after that when we were in Lee, that was Sir Malcolm Smith, Sir Watson was a Unionist and he allowed them to have his meeting in the hall - probably in Sir }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 Watson\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
 hall. And the next time it was a Liberal member that was on and he stayed in Lee Garth you know for the weekend but he had his meeting up in the school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 In the 1920's. Yes. Further on. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or their house if they voted differently from their employers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, not here because you see well they had their croft and as long as you could pay the rent then that was all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So you don't remember any political activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 No, no, very, very little. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well they were never idle. Always knitting to do you see in the evening once the tea t
hings was washed and away then they get on with - you usually have the spinning wheel you know and spin the very fine threads and then they would knit that into fine shawls, maybe two yards could go through a wedding ring. And - well when I started to kni
t was just when I was maybe eight, seven or eight, and it was the fine yard but not so very fine and - we made fine - well like - shawls you know, we called them scarves, and the fine shawls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And that's what the women did with all their spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. Yes, all their spare time usually was spent knitting. That was their means of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 livelihood}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well I told you the other day, he used to - when the corn was dried and the rigs after being cut he took it in the 
barn and thrashed it and in the evening then he made straw ropes, and that was for thatching the houses with and also for winding round the scoops in the yard. And they made sort of reeds, that was what they called floss and they dried that and wound thin
ner ropes for making the kishies that brought home the peats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 For putting on the pines backs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So that's how he spent his spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. Yes. Yes, yes. Making straw ropes and then the thinner ones out of the - like bent for makin
g the kishies for the - bring home the peats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your mother have any }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 interest}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  outside the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 She went to the knitting party organised by the minister's wife, that kind of thing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes. Well you see they 
always had their knitting with them and knitted while the guild was going on, Mrs Campbell'd read a story while they were doing their knitting. Then we had a cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, well they would take their knitt
ing and go to other folks houses you know, sit and talk, and then some of the neighbours would bring their knitting and talk in our house. But they never sat idle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did she go out by herself to other peoples houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Not with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, the women usually went with their knitting you see. He sometimes went maybe but further away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So she'd have gone with her sister, your aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And perhaps with you as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. When we grew a bit bigger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When did your father get home from work in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You see he was always working on the croft.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 It doesn't really apply?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How many evenings a week would he spend at home, would he ever go out in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Ve
ry seldom. Used to maybe ago and visit some of me mother's brother lived - well - a piece away down there, occasionally mummy and him to visit up there. But - most of the evenings was spent home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 There wasn't a pub on the island was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were there any clubs for the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 men}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about down at the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
No, but that was only the later years that they started to play billiards. No, no, there were none of that before them - after the second world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 He didn't take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, they used to play football over the links on Christmas Day, that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 That was just the young men?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, just the young men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did either of your parents belong to anything like a savings club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Nothing of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Funeral club or a sickness club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How did you get on with your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Get on all right. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When you were a child who did you play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well you see I 
played with her and then Charlie Roberts was the neighbours and Annie used to come over and play with us and then we would go over and play with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So that was with your neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Where did you play, just round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Around about the house and we would go down to the sand you see and build sand castles.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 It was very nice having a beach near at hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, oh yes, we often went down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You went into your neighbour's homes as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, yes, we could go in anytime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What games did you play, were there any particular games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No. Don't think there was any special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You made sandcastles and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But you didn't }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 play}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  any special }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 children\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 ' games that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, when the schools was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 built}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  in the yard in the winter we used to play hide and seek around the schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What are they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 The - cordon schools you know up in the yard, and stocks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 We call them stacks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. Yes. The Shetlander schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh not too bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But your parents didn't get angry if you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no,. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were you free to play with anyone you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Your parents didn't discourage you from playing with certain children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you belong to any youth organisations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No. No. Nothing unless we went to guild. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 Women\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  Guild.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 That was for the older women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, maybe -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 It wasn't just for girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, maybe sixteen or seventeen then you could go to the guild.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Sixteen and seventeen upwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When you had a bit of spare time was there anything you did except for knitting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
We learned to crochet at school, you knew, the cotton and then we - we learned to sew to at the school and - well, we made small garments for - we had doll and made dolls garments and that sort of thing when we grew a bit bigger and then - oh we tried to 
make small things for ourselves when we got further on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you keep any pets or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 We had a dog and a cat. And maybe more cats sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But you didn't have anything of your own specially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no. We had a dog and a cat and we used to - we one time had a she dog and she used to have puppies and we used to keep one usually.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you go fishing or for walks or bicycling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, we never had bicycles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You didn't take part in any sport?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your parents give you any pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Very little.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 We would maybe got a penny or two now and again but we didn't have money to spare you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 It wasn't regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 If you did get a bit of money what did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well if you got a penny you may have bought sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You said your mother's sister helped in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 There was nobody else who came in to help her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh well me auntie always did the work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. Me mother had a brother and his family lived - well across the other side of the valley for the Post Office. And
 we often used to visit them and they visited us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were those the only close relations you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. You see my father came from Unst and so most of the relations on that side was way over in Unst.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So this way you're a bit different from the other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, well - yes. Well we had a few relations.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How often did you see your relations then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we could see them any time we wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How often did you actually go to see them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Maybe once a fortnight or something. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 In each others homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Your parents had friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes, they were quite friendly with folk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Where did they see them, they saw each other all the time didn't they I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, yes. They were meeting usually during the day sometime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your mother and father have the same friends or did they have different friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, they were usually just much the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But you mentioned before the women were together in one group and the men in another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, when - when the - well if there are any functions on or that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 If they went out to visit neighbours or friends would your mother and father go together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, they would go together. They would just talk and yarn away while they were knitting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So it wasn't just your mother going out by herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no. Father went with her sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And your parents friends came to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How often would you have visitors in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh maybe once or twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 In the evening that would be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Would they be offered anything to eat or drink?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Nothing to drink but they always had a cup of tea and maybe -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No alcohol you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, there was no alcohol.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 They'd have a cup of tea though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, tea and maybe biscuits or scone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Was there any particular days or occasions when they came, when you had friends in
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, it was just whenever they pleased. When the weather was suitable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And these friends were much your mother's as your father's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
People often tell us that in those days people made their own amusements, what did your parents do when they got together with their friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Well, it was usually just talking, you see, some folk would play the fiddle and - that's the violin, but my folk couldn't. And - we had no other musical instrument.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Your parents didn't play musical instruments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But some of the people round here did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What kind of things would they do together, apart from knitting, would they play games of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well they played this cards sometimes you know, just simple card games and draughts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Would they tell stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes, yes, plenty old stories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 People spent quite a lot of time doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, they could knit you see and talk and tell the stories at the same time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Not many people remember these stories now?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well likely no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Many people }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 divide}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  society into different social classes or groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, you see here they were all very much the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But not everyone because there were the landlords weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, but they didna interfere much with the folk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But of the people on the island were they really all the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well some maybe had a bit more money but usually it was all just very much the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about you and your family, you were just much the same as everybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, yes, much the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 This was basically as crofters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, all crofters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But what about other people, can you remember being brought up to
 treat people of one sort differently to another, were you ever taught to curtsey or show respect in some way to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well you see we always showed more courtesy to the minister and his wife and to the Laird when he would come around, but there wa
s no resident doctor in this island. And we only got a resident nurse after Sir Watson interceded for one. There was nine children born here in 1922 and he was here on the island then and thought this wasna good enough without a nurse so we got a nurse to
 Fetlar before the National Health come on. We used to have a nursing association.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But how did you show respect to these people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well bid them good morning and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You didn't curtsey?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Was there anyone you called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 We always said sir and madam to Mrs - Mr and Mrs Campbell.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 That's the minister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, and to the Laird if we met him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about the teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes. He - Br. Brown the teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 People didn't show respect to your parents in that kind of way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Who were considered the most important people on the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well the ministers you see and there was a U.F. minister who stayed over in the East Manse where you are now. But he 
was a bachelor so you see - Mr McCarbur.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And the minister here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Mr Campbell and Mrs Campbell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Anybody else, what about the teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well he was a Fetlar man and he wasn't with me but he made very scholars and he lived over in the schoolhouse. He was a bachelor then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You came into contact with these people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you come into contact with the Laird?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No. Not at all unless they went over there to pay the rent and do his work at times but I never was over in his mansion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about the shopkeepers, who did they associate with, were they separate from everybody else or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, just the - we all went to the same school and they all mixed together you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about the children of the ministers, did they go to the same schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, they went to the same school here for a short time and then they went onto the school in Lerwick. And - Mr }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 Campbell\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  oldest son passed to be a ship's captain. And his second son was a doctor, he was Do
ctor Campbell. He was in Lerwick practice for several years. And the younger son, I really don't know what he did but - he - was in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 Sumatra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  at the time that the war started and he moved over to New Zealand when the Japs was coming there and he had one daug
hter was married to a minister in Bressay and another daughter married Doctor Turnbull and they were out in New Zealand. So -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Was there any difference in the kind of people who went to church }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 and}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  went to the Church of Scotland here and the United Free?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Free. Yes, one lot used to go one kirk and the other lot to the other kirk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Was there any difference in the kind of people who went to each?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, just all - the same but only they belonged to different sections.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Why did one lot belong to one and one to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No special reasons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no special reasons really because it's all the Bible. It's the same music and all but only - that's been you see since this }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 eruption}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 This eruption, that was, oh I don't know how long. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
You see the Church of Scotland and the U.F. were supposed to have been united in about 1929 and - but - some of the old folk is now still united. But it doesn't really matter now the generations are no bothering about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 On th
e island here did all the people, except for the minister and so on, have the same standard of living or would you say there were different groups among them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, it was all very much the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 There weren't some who were better off than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well maybe slightly some folk maybe they had - their families had had a bit more money before them but usually it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4195931\charrsid4750000 was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  all just the same sort of living. Crofting. Fishermen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 There wasn't any group of people who felt themselves a bit superior to the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, I don't think so really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 There weren't any families that people thought of as rough?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Families which had a bad reputation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, they were all very much the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And both your mother and father thought of themselves as being crofters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Was it possible at that time to move from one group to another, to better yourself in anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes, you could move from the one croft to the other if you wanted to, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 If people wanted to improve themselves or make themselves better off, what could they do, if someone was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 ambitious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  or had hopes for their children what might they do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well - well you see the young men then, most of them all went to the Merchant Navy and if
 they were well enough educated or felt inclined they tried to get up you see to be Merchant Navy Officers. Quite a lot of them were. And - well maybe one or two of them went for engineers and this - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 Wilily}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  and Tommy's father, he went to be a joiner in Lerwick you see and - well, some of them went to the boot trades as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So if there was a young man who wanted to improve himself that's what he'd do, he'd try to go in the Navy and become and officer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes. Yes, yes, a lot of them went to - to the sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You know quite a number of people who improved themselves in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Oh yes, yes, a lot of them went and joined the - well, there used to be the - well seaman serve, they call it the Merchant Navy now. Lots of the Shetland men were - and after the first world war they used to go to the whaling, away down yonder in south }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 Georgia}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
. And they said there were three hundred Shetlanders that used to go down there. And they made quite a good living for a few months you see and then they coul
d come back and work their crofts in the spring, in the summer. Then the Russians and the Japs, they went down there too and got far too many and made the whales nearly extinct and they now do not have the whaling. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Can you remember any crofters sons who went to college or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Well the Shuans you see, he was Arthur's - grave in a way, his daughter went to Lerwick to school and went onto training college in Aberdeen. And the oldest son, he was down in learning to be a draughtsm
an on the Clyde. But - the ordinary fold didna ha' enough money you see to put them on to that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Not really. Only some with better manners maybe when - than the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you remember anyone being described that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, not really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Not the minister or the Laird or anyone like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, the minister was a fine old man. Very kind and so was she. They had a real interest in the folk of the parish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you remember seeing a policeman round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Very seldom. No, no, not as a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 child}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 Very, very seldom.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Can you remember ever seeing one then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, I remember seeing one - well - sometime about the beginning of the war or that, I don't know what he was doing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did you think of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 He was a fine looking man - tall fine looking man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When you were naughty your mother didn't say, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How do you think the policeman treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Oh they treated them very well but only I mean he wasn't - there were no drunken brawls or anything like that here. Yes. No, there was no drink going on here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Was your home rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes, we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 paid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
 six guineas a year to the Laird for the croft you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You didn't ever see anything of the landlord yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Well no, he didn't come around to visit us. We maybe saw - we saw him at the kirk on Sunday, he used to drive to the kirk in a pony and trap. Oh beard, with a white beard you know, and a tall hat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did you think about him as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh well - he was all right in some ways but he did not do much for to improve his tenants. That's true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What didn't he do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well he never gave him any help to improve their houses. They had to do that themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 A good landlord would have done that you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What other feelings did people have about the landlord, this was Sir Arthur Nicholson?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. Well they stood rather in awe. R
ather I think. And you see, they had to go and do his work when he asked them to, they had to go and drive his sheep and - his ponies and cows and all that. Oh he had all - lot of stock you know at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did they mind doing that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, they thought always a few shillings for doing it. But wasna very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you remember feeling that your parents had a struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well rather they did. But they were always quite happy and - I mean we were never in debt. That was one - we never were in debt so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But some families were in debt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, they might have been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What difference did it make to the family if your father was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well he was never really ill. He suffered from heart disease when 
we - when he was turned to be an old man you know but he was never ill as long as his working years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you ever have to get help from anybody?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 From any charity or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 If someone on the island did something the people disapproved of did they show their disapproval in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well maybe - sometimes but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How would they show it, what might they disapprove of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well you see there was nothing serious to disapprove of. Not in my day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 My impression of the island is that it is quite a tightly knit community.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, it is mostly all related you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 All related to each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, mostly all related.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But they didn't have any sort of standards amongst themselves which people had to keep up to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about going to church on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well most of the folk went to church on Sunday anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What if somebody didn't go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh well - they werena - blacklisted for that you know. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 There wasn't anything called rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, there was nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were you given lessons by one of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, we used to learn to - we - most of the children could read their alphabet and that before they went to school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Who taught you that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 My father and me mother. They could both read you see and - I could read the small words, the three letter words when I went to school.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How old were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 I went to school when I was six past. We had to walk across the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 fields}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 . There was no road then. And no cars.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Not like today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What time did you have to get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 We had to be there - ten o'clock in the morning. We had to be school at ten o'clock in the morning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What time did you start off to get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 We started off about a quarter past nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 it took you three quarters of an hour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 We come back at half past two - we were out of the school at half past two in the winter and four on the summer.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So school didn't last very long really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
No. then we had a break you see about midday and we'd take our piece along with us. And when I was at school then - it was Mr Brown, he was a Fetlar 
man and we used to well learn songs, you know, and some could recite pieces of poetry, and then we had a concert and with the proceeds of the concert they bought some coal so we got a cup of hot cocoa along with our piece in the winter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What was your piece?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well a piece of bread with butter on it from home you see. And we had a good meal when we got home in the afternoon.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 This was the one school on the island which everybody went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, everyone went to the same school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And you walked to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, they all walked to school then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And it took you about three quarters of an hour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Who did you go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 My sister and I and John and Iona.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 They were neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh I liked the school all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You didn't dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no I never disliked it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did you like about school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 I liked history. And arithmetic then. I'd no use for drawing. No, I didn't care for drawing. I wasna artistic.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh I well we liked our teacher fine, he was very agreeable with us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Was there only one teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well you see there was a - local girl was assistant. Mrs Jamie
son - she was ten and a half then, she was young, she was assistant teacher to a Scottish lady that was there when I went first, Miss McLeod. But she was left before this first world war and Mr Brown taught all the war years. And he had Ellen Williamson f
or a second rate teacher. And - then after he left we had a Miss Kilman from up in Nairn. That was the class of my day.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You had quite a number of teachers altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, we had three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you like them all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, now we liked them all. We got on very well with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So there were two classes in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Yes, the - the - headmaster taught the high - the older pupils and the - sub - teachers taught the small ones. But the last years that I was at school there were only one teacher for the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 bairns
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  was gradually getting fewer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, like manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes. Now Mr Brown was very - an he was very religious we always had our Bible lesson every m
orning and told the Lord's prayer and we recited psalms you know and then we could tell the whole psalm to end up with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What kind of things did he tell you were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh well just a - essentials of life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Things like manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, oh yes, we had to have manners.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What were good manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well - please and thank you and - well - sort of reverence to our elders and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about tidiness and punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes, we had to be there at the time and we had to be tidy. Just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well you see we were supposed to speak English in school as best we could and then we could talk the dialect outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So he did try to make you speak not the dialect?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no. No, we spoke English in school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 There was a difference between how you spoke in school and how you spoke outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes, yes. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 You see it's not here in a lot of the old Shetland. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 It's dying away now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you think there's less difference now between the way people speak in school than the way they speak at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well not so much now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 There was much more difference in your day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes. Much more different, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well the boys got the strap. But - well the classes was never punished like that. No, no. we never did anything very serious.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But there must have been some girls who weren't perfect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, but we never - I never saw anyone getting thrashing or anything like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But were there any punishments for girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, well they were made maybe sit and write a few lines you know, something like that but nothing serious.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So the punishment for girls was writing lines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, well something on that line. Or - maybe doing some work - but there was never any case of the strap in my day for girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What kind of things would they get punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well - if they were naughty. They maybe didna learn their lesson very well and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What does naughty mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well - maybe speaking when they shouldna have been speaking and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes. Yes, yes, they wanted us to do the best we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Yes, yes, and they - we - they had - hear our lesson at night, you see, we got lessons to learn at home. Yes, now we had to have our lesson ready for next day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your parents help you with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
Yes, well they - they couldn't help us much you know when we got on to learning - higher things but early reading and all that they saw that we got all that done before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, not much. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did they meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, the teachers used to come and visit us quite often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Was that socially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, not just socially.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So your parents were friendly with the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, very friendly with the teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 The other children at the school came from the same kind of home as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. Yes, just the same, much the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did the ministers children go to school when you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You see, they were long grown up and away before my day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 The Laird children didn't go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, they were never at this school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Would you say the teachers singled out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No I don't think so. No, they were very fair.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 There weren't favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, not really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What about if some of the children were particularly clever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well they - you see, they didna have much chance of getting on, we just all had the same lessons and - and some were of course a bit clevere
r than others but - well, they couldn't do anything about it could they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no. We wee re all the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 The boys didn't go into gangs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Were there any children who were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid926604\charrsid4750000 left}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Everyone was in it together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 I left school at fourteen and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Would you have stayed longer if you had had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No I don't
 think - you had to leave and help them in the croft at home and there was nothing more for me to learn at this school and I couldn't afford to go anywhere else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you ever attend any part time education afterwards, like evening classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes. And benefit from domestic service later on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 While you were at school did you have any part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Or any means of earning a little extra money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, just help on the croft you see when we come home in the evenings and getting home the peats in the summer holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But did you get paid for bringing in the peats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no. Unless maybe some of the boys did it for some of the other neighbours then they might have gotten a few shillings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 But not the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What was the first full time job you had?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well, I went to Sir Watson Chayne as kitchen maid and the end of August 1920.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So you left school when you were fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And then you were at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, until I was eighteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And Sir Watson }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4195931\charrsid4750000 Chayne}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  was here on the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. He was in - you see, I was never with them in London, I was no old enough for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And what were you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 I was kitchen maid for three years and then the other six and a half I was housemaid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes, yes, no, we lived in. Lived in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So your first job was with Sir Watson }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4195931\charrsid4750000 Chayne}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  here on the island?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 That was your first job in 1920?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And then you had another job with him when you were promoted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Oh yes, you see I was three years kitchen maid and then after that I was housemaid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Up 'til when?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 1930 we }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4195931\charrsid4750000 left}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
 there and the house was shut up at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well then I come home you see to help me parents in the croft. And then me sister got married and I was there for a wh
ile until me mother died you see and - and then after me nephew got married I went South }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4195931\charrsid4750000 and}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
 I was four and a half years in Leicester, Whetstone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You were in service there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 From when 'til when was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 '61 and four and a half years I went in September '61 and - would have been - I come back here in - about the beginning of 1966.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And you've been here housekeeping at that Manse since, for the last four years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did you do between when your mother died, when did she die?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 She died in 1951 and then you see my sister was ill and so I looked her and brought up the two boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So that kept you busy all through the second war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes. Yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 There were not paid jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, I didn't get no money for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Would you have preferred a different kind of job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You didn't have any special training for any of these jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no. Just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You didn't belong to any kind of trade union or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Would you say that doing this kind of domestic service full time work, did it change your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 It didn't make a big difference to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 
No, no, no. I got a bit of - more experience down in England, saw different places. Then they wrote and asked me you see to come back here to the Manse, 'cos there was nobody to look after }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4195931\charrsid4750000 Mr.
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  McWilliam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You went on living at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Up 'til 1920?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When you went into service here on the island with Sir Watson }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4195931\charrsid4750000 Chayne}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did starting full time work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, No, I went home on me evenings out you see and Sunday afternoons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you spend your Sunday any differently?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we were never - did anything but what was necessary on Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 So Sundays were the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 As they always had been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you take any interest in politics yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No. Not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 I asked you before how you spent your spare time, did this change at all when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 When you got older there weren't any changes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, we just helped on the croft you see and did knitting in the evenings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 You didn't go out anywhere in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well we would take our knitting you see and go to the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4195931\charrsid4750000  nrighbours\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000  houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 And being on the island you didn't meet any new friends at this stage of your life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, not many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you have any special friends at this time, boy friends or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, I didn't have - we were quite friendly with all the lads around but nothing special.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your parents expect to know where you were if you were going out in the evening to see some people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Yes, well we always told them where we were going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did you have to be home by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, but we always back by eleven o'clock at night usually.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Did your sister have any full time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, she always worked on the croft you see and did knitting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 She didn't go into service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 No, no, she always worked the croft and then got married. It was Thomas John's father that she married the 
second time. You see, his mother died and then his father married my sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 What did her husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid264984 AP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 Well he was just a crofter as well and he worked for Sir - Arthur Nicholson you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5984097 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2180184\charrsid4750000 He worked for him?
